NIST CSF Function	Purpose	Key Activities	Example
Govern	Establish cybersecurity strategy, policies, and oversight.	• Security policies
• Risk management
• Compliance
• Roles & responsibilities
• Executive oversight
• Third-party risk management	Create a company cybersecurity policy requiring annual security awareness training.
Identify	Understand what assets exist and what risks they face.	• Asset inventory
• Software inventory
• Data classification
• Risk assessments
• Critical systems identification	Maintain an inventory of all company laptops, servers, applications, and cloud services.
Protect	Implement safeguards to reduce the likelihood and impact of cyberattacks.	• Access control
• Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
• Encryption
• Security awareness training
• Patch management
• Firewalls
• Backups	Require MFA for all employee accounts and keep systems updated with security patches.
Detect	Identify cybersecurity events as quickly as possible.	• Continuous monitoring
• Log analysis
• Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS)
• SIEM tools
• Threat monitoring	Detect repeated failed login attempts from an unusual location.
Respond	Take action to contain and manage cybersecurity incidents.	• Incident response planning
• Containment
• Investigation
• Communication
• Malware removal
• Evidence collection	Isolate an infected computer to stop ransomware from spreading across the network.
Recover	Restore operations after an incident and improve future resilience.	• Disaster recovery
• Business continuity
• Data restoration
• Lessons learned
• Security improvements	Restore systems from backups and update security procedures after an incident.
